docs.abstract: The uproar over voting seems almost an inevitable development in the race, which pits two candidates on opposite sides of the nation’s voting wars.
docs.snippet: The uproar over voting seems almost an inevitable development in the race, which pits two candidates on opposite sides of the nation’s voting wars.
docs.lead_paragraph: ATLANTA — Reports that tens of thousands of Georgia voters, predominantly African-Americans, were placed on a list for further scrutiny have exploded into the Georgia governor’s race, leading to bitter exchanges between the candidates and leaving many residents uncertain what to expect as the state began early voting Monday.

headline.main: Showdown in Georgia Governor’s Race Reflects a Larger Fight Over Voting Rights
headline.print_headline: Showdown in Georgia Reflects a Larger Fight Over Voting Rights

docs.lead_paragraph: LAS VEGAS — John Toles-Bey wants to be clear: He loves Barack Obama.

headline.main: Fight Fire With Fire, or Be Civil With Trump? The Obama Coalition Is Unsure
headline.print_headline: Obama Uplifted Them. Now They Want to Fight.

docs.abstract: In the state primary Tuesday, voters will elect a successor to the longtime representative John Conyers Jr., choosing among one of the most diverse and competitive fields of candidates this year.
docs.snippet: In the state primary Tuesday, voters will elect a successor to the longtime representative John Conyers Jr., choosing among one of the most diverse and competitive fields of candidates this year.
docs.lead_paragraph: DETROIT — A Palestinian-American woman in the Michigan legislature running in the mold of Bernie Sanders. The African-American president of the Detroit City Council, who is popular with unions. The white mayor of a nearby suburb, positioning himself as a pragmatist. Two black state senators from historically prominent political families.

headline.main: Michigan Is About to Elect a Very Different Member of Congress
headline.print_headline: Change Is Coming to a District That’s Been Waiting for It

docs.abstract: Many residents are now wary of politicians from both parties and government at large because no one seemed able to mitigate the city’s crisis.
docs.snippet: Many residents are now wary of politicians from both parties and government at large because no one seemed able to mitigate the city’s crisis.
docs.lead_paragraph: FLINT, Mich. — The first car arrived around 3:30 a.m., more than six hours before the weekly “help center” opened at a local church. David Brooks, a 72-year-old retired General Motors laborer, was in the second car in the queue, and passed the time by sleeping in the back seat of his refurbished 1997 Chevy Santa Fe, as has become his Thursday routine since 2014 — the last time his Flint community trusted its water.

headline.main: Michigan Governor’s Race Tests Flint’s Jaded Residents
headline.print_headline: Candidates Make Their Case in Town Where Mistrust Runs Deep

docs.abstract: A glowing jobs report right before an election should be a gift to the party in power, but the president’s strident tone on immigration is drowning out the good news.
docs.snippet: A glowing jobs report right before an election should be a gift to the party in power, but the president’s strident tone on immigration is drowning out the good news.
docs.lead_paragraph: In normal political times, a glowing report on the nation’s economy just before Election Day would be a gift to the party in power and a uniform talking point for its candidates. But entering the final weekend before Tuesday’s midterm vote, President Trump’s blistering message of nativist fear has become the dominant theme of the campaign’s last days, threatening to overshadow the good economic news.

headline.main: Republicans Have a Humming Economy to Tout, but Trump Rhetoric Muddies the Message
headline.print_headline: Trump’s Theme Is Outshining  Election Gold

byline.original: By Astead W. Herndon and Sydney Ember

docs.abstract: Ms. Valdez is a Latina, a lesbian and the Democratic nominee for governor. But some activists on the left say she’s not worthy of their support, particularly because of her record on immigration.
docs.snippet: Ms. Valdez is a Latina, a lesbian and the Democratic nominee for governor. But some activists on the left say she’s not worthy of their support, particularly because of her record on immigration.
docs.lead_paragraph: AUSTIN, Tex. — Even in the close-knit circles of Texas liberals, Lupe Valdez, the Democratic nominee for governor, conjures up a disparate set of opinions — far from the united front the candidate wants to evoke.

headline.main: In Texas Governor’s Race, Lupe Valdez Faces Resistance From Fellow Democrats
headline.print_headline: Some Texas Democrats Wary of Party’s Nominee for Governor

docs.abstract: A flurry of ballot measures on Election Day were the latest move to reshape how we vote, and who can cast a ballot.
docs.snippet: A flurry of ballot measures on Election Day were the latest move to reshape how we vote, and who can cast a ballot.
docs.lead_paragraph: Amid the recounts, recriminations and allegations of voter suppression or ballot fraud, something else happened in Tuesday’s elections — a wave of actions aimed at making voting easier and fairer that is an often-overlooked strain in the nation’s voting wars.

headline.main: Before the Fights Over Recounts: An Election Day Vote on Voting
headline.print_headline: Among the Winners: Expanded Voting and Fairer Elections

docs.abstract: Since releasing the results in October, the ancestry issue clouding her possible presidential campaign has only intensified.
docs.snippet: Since releasing the results in October, the ancestry issue clouding her possible presidential campaign has only intensified.
docs.lead_paragraph: WASHINGTON — The plan was straightforward: After years of being challenged by President Trump and others about a decades-old claim of Native American ancestry, Senator Elizabeth Warren of Massachusetts would take a DNA test to prove her stated family origins in the Cherokee and Delaware tribes.

headline.main: Elizabeth Warren Stands by DNA Test. But Around Her, Worries Abound.
headline.print_headline: Warren Facing Cloud of Anger Over DNA Test
